# Semi-Active Suspension Modeling & Control â€“ Simulink Quarter-Car

This project builds and compares passive vs. semi-active suspension systems using a quarter-car Simulink model. A PID-controlled variable damper is used to improve ride quality and stability over road disturbances.

(Source: *Project 2.5 PDF*, MSPE 29800, Purdue University) :contentReference[oaicite:3]{index=3}

